Although we observed values directly for b, we also parameterized assimilability of nutrients ζb as variable dependent on availability of phytoplanktonic organisms to absorb nutrients, which is regulated by transparency, pH, and temperature of water. We excluded water transparency as independent variable of ζb because the studied lake was noncolored and shallow enough to be entirely penetrated by light, and water transparency was rather correlated to the amount of phytoplankton particles. Thus, we modeled b + ζb as2bt+ζbt=βt+y1·TPt+y2·P-PO4t+y3·N-NO3t+y4·N-NH4t·+y5·TPt×tempt+y6·TPt×pHt+y7·P-PO4t×tempt+y8·P-PO4t×pHt+y9·N-NO3t×tempt+y10·N-NO3t×pHt+y11·N-NH4t×tempt+y12·N-NH4t+error\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
